reviews.reviewText: overall great product! i’m 19 and i’ve been feeling a little crappy lately from being in college and not being able to eat as healthy as i should be. these have made me feel a lot better!! the ONLY issue with these are the smell… absolutely repulsive. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finally found a decent multivitamin
reviews.reviewText: We've spent hours searching for a multivitamin without riboflavin since my daughter already gets way too much of it in a migraine supplement. We finally found these. Wish they were in pill form because that's just easier, but the taste of these isn't too bad (the 2 grams of added sugar certainly help).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My daughter LOVES
reviews.reviewText: My daughter has taken these everyday for about a month and already loves them. The last time I ordered teen gummies they all melted together. These do not. They don’t taste to bad and my daughter isn’t as crabby and tired all the time. Last month I saw an add for these and thought they could help. My daughter gets stressed very easily and can become crabby and extremely tired. She has a lot of school work and that can be too much for a teen girl. She told me she feels less stressed and less exhausted everyday like usually when taking these gummies. Glad something finally helped. They only problem you might have is the taste but I recommend!!
